Another trip around the sun for me and my Sagittarius twin flame @carisfawcett.

With a one/two punch of Dec 18th and Dec 19th, it's a challenge to make them individual events, so we've embraced celebrating together. And damn is there a lot to celebrate about this woman, who makes life infinitely more fun and spontaneous. From the Serengeti plains to renaissance festivals, the castles and grouse moors of Scotland to our favorite Dallas dive bar, Caris is sure to be wide-eyed, prepared with fun facts, and for sure the best dressed.

I'm lucky to have a woman of this caliber by my side, which is the best birthday gift I could ever hope for. Make sure you send her well wishes for her 30th. Cheers everybody!

We've got a unique giveaway for you through @modernhuntsman.
⁠
You can win this one-of-a-kind, realistic-looking Replica Elk Mount upholstered in Pendleton wool fabric ($1500 value), made by Oregon artist @sethpatterson - AND a copy of Modern Huntsman Volume 10. Just to be clear, the elk skull and antlers are not from a real animal - they are a “replica” euro mount, but on the wall it's hard to distinguish from the real thing. The mount fits flush on a wall, comes with an easy-to-install wall mounting bracket and measures approximately 46” wide by 56” tall, with an antler depth of roughly 22”. This piece of art will demand attention in any room and bring both a modern and rustic charm to your home.⁠
⁠

1. Be following @modernhuntsman on Instagram⁠
2. Be an email subscriber of Modern Huntsman (sign up at link in bio) ⁠

Here's a recent story that I shot and wrote about the the incredible waterfowl lodge called @skyfallreserve that my old friend @steverokks operates. It's really hard to describe what all this place is, but it has something for everyone, and is only about an hour south of Dallas.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
So proud of the Rokks family for their continual evolution, and we're lucky to have their focus and drive now pointed at conservation and habitat management. Produced in partnership with our friends from @duckcampco, a  link to the story is in my bio.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Hope you enjoy the read, and if you're thinking of visiting, you should hop on it quick because many dates for 2023 and early 2024 are already booked. Cheers everybody!

From the Archive - Tanzania, March 2015⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
This was day one of seven on my trek to the top of Kilimanjaro. After I took this photo, I remember thinking "how the hell are we gonna get up there?" The answer to that question was one of the many wise and simple phrases in Swahili, "pole pole" — slowly, slowly.

Devils' Bridge in Sedona, Arizona from awhile back when @carisfawcett and I had the place to ourselves. It's a pretty eerie feeling to stand on what feels like a thin suspended rock bridge, but I'm sure the architects knew what they were doing, so it was fine. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Trying to find time to dig through the archive and post more, as I'd venture to guess that I've never posted 85-90% of the things I've shot in the past 10 years. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Don't feel like much of a photographer anymore, but it's always nice to look back at images I've created over the years and remember being very inspired at the time. Thanks for hanging around on this dusty old account!

"We entered the forest before dawn, and the fog hung thick and heavy with no whisper of wind."
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Excerpt from a story I wrote in Volume 5 of @modernhuntsman back when we had themes. This was the "traditions" issue, and my contribution was about the time I spent in Hungary and Romania learning about their hunting cultures and various rituals. Certainly hope to go back in the near future, it was an incredible experience. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Thanks for the photos Danny ( @theurbanhuntsman ), and for the constant shit-talking under your breath in the background.

Our old friend and collaborator @tylersharpphoto is BACK. 

After spending several years in Montana he’s home in Texas! It’s been great catching up with him and hearing stories of his epic adventures.

So much has happened since we created this video with Tyler in 2016. Namely, the creation and success of @modernhuntsman. Tyler is still a shining example of cutting the rope beneath you and making it happen. 

#thinkbranded #modernhuntsman #brandfilm
#filmmaking #hunting

If you’re anywhere near Austin, Texas, I wanted to extend an invitation to a @modernhuntsman film screening we’re hosting on Sunday April 23rd at the AFS Cinema. Limited tickets are at the link in my bio.

“El Observador” follows wildlife cinematographer Austin Alvarado and his relationship to nature through his work pursuing black bears in Far West Texas. Our crew worked really hard on this, and the results are incredible. Hope you can join us there!

The film is presented by @swarovskioptik_outdoor with additional support from @lonestarbeer & @kinglandwater

A girl and her shotgun.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I wrote a story about surprising @carisfawcett with a 20 gauge beauty from the @berettagallery this past Christmas, the adventures that have ensued, and how it's brought us closer. It's very personal, but I think I'm gonna include it in the next issue of @modernhuntsman.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Regardless, it's pretty clear that my days as top shooter in the house are numbered.

Many favorite photographs I've taken and words I've written are from time spent in Tanzania. There is something grounding, inspiring and challenging about being in a remote bush camp that seems to draw it out, and I'm really looking forward to going back this summer to spend some time with @robin_hurt_safaris. Definitely missing my safari days.

I wouldn't call myself a wildlife filmmaker, but @byronjpace could probably get away with that title after he chose the perfect location to install the @voskertech cameras to capture wildlife.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I've been monitoring my 8 acres property in Dallas remotely until I can get development approved, and was surprised to find a burly bobcat strolling around our trailer. There have also been deer, raccoons and the odd guinea fowl that must be loose and on the run.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Otherwise, there is not much progress to report on the land thus far, as life and work have pulled me in other directions. But the good news is that these cameras have beefed up security to the point that there have been no more incidents of trespassing or illegal dumping. Thanks again to the @voskertech team for getting me set up. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
If you have a remote property without power, these are great options that run on solar and transmit over a cellular network.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Hope to be back with more updates soon, and which will eventually involve building a dream home in the woods.

For those of you who were not able to attend the sold out screening of film ‘El Observador’ a few weeks ago, we’re excited to share the full version on the @swarovskioptik_outdoor website.

This @modernhuntsman short documentary follows wildlife cinematographer @austintorios in pursuit of black bears in West Texas, and addresses the comeback of the species in a harsh desert region. It is a visually stunning journey through the Big Bend region that highlights the incredible resilience of black bears. We hope that the film sparks a greater conversation around the importance of our relationship with wildlife in this great state and beyond.

Presented by @swarovskioptik_outdoor, this film had additional support from @lonestarbeer and  @kinglandwater.

You can view the full version at the link in my bio, and we hope you enjoy this unique perspective into wildlife filmmaking.

Spent some time last weekend at my favorite small-town Texas lake in Nocona, testing out the Fuji X-Pro 3 and laughing at this ridiculous water monster named Wyatt.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I'm trying to get back into the "art of shooting" after so many years of a professional slog. Such a fun manual camera with some really cool classic film presets, and it certainly helps to have a willing model on hand.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Hope to share more soon with upcoming trips to Montana, Tanzania, and Kenya, so please hold me to it.

Safariancé.

After six months of careful planning, espionage and misdirection, I just pulled off the surprise of a lifetime and proposed to @carisfawcett in my favorite place in the world — the wilds of Tanzania.

With the help of my dear friend Lupo, I sourced a rare gemstone native to Tanzania called Tsavorite, and had the ring made in secret before we arrived. I snuck it in my bag on the way into camp, distracted her by saying we were taking marketing photos, and caught her COMPLETELY by surprise as the sun set behind the acacia trees. After cursing at me in shock, she said yes. I’ll share that hilarious video another time, but for now we could not be happier to be engaged and in this beautiful, wild place for the next week.

Thank you to our friends who helped keep the secret, and a massive thank you to Roger & Daisy Hurt for helping me make this so special for Caris. I have dreamed of proposing here since I first stepped foot in Tanzania in 2006, and that dream is now a perfect reality. We’ll share more soon, but for now we’re off to the bush for a classic East African hunting safari.

Today, love wins.

SCOTLAND TRIP OPENING⁠

We have one spot for a hunter + guest open for our @modernhuntsman trip to the Scottish Highlands from Sept 24th-Oct 1st. 

Red stag stalking, Atlantic salmon fly fishing, grouse hunting with pointing dogs, chef-cooked meals, daily scotch tastings, and incredible scenery. It is going to be one incredible adventure, and we hope you can join us.

You can get more info and reserve the last ticket at the link in my bio.

NEW FILM for @modernhuntsman 

In our ongoing partnership with @lonestarbeer, we’re telling four stories about interesting Texans who live in close connection with the wildlife and wild places in the Lone Star State.

The first film features our friend Ben Paschal and his adventurous life of fly fishing on the Laguna Madre — one of the most unique and important hypersaline lagoon ecosystems in the United States.

The Lure of the Laguna releases next Tuesday 8/15.
A long time ago, on a cold Montana day.

The first film in our four-part @modernhuntsman x @lonestarbeer  series is now live. 

Chapter One, The Lure of the Laguna, is about angling savant Ben Paschal and his obsession with salt water fly fishing on the coast of Texas. It’s a story about hard work, dedication, and bailing on the internship his parents wanted him to take to follow his passion in the Laguna Madre.

It’s an honor to tell stories about those who care so deeply about wildlife and wild places in the Lone Star State, and hopefully you find some inspiration within the adventure. Really fun working with @jongarrettrob and @david.zuccarelli on this one. More to come soon. 

The full film is at the link in my bio.

We're excited to announce the cover of @modernhuntsman Volume 11.

This intriguing photo by our good friend @dirtlord is from our feature story on Mark McNair, a renowned duck decoy carver. Many say he is the best in the world.

Our team puts a lot of thought into these selections, making sure to add something interesting to our previous 10 covers. We felt that Paul's modern take on such a classic subject was a perfect addition. ⁠
⁠
Pre-orders are open if you want to reserve a copy, but the best thing to do is subscribe. You get 2 books a year, access to our entire archive, and 20% off back issues. ⁠Books will ship in September.⁠ Both links are in my bio. 
⁠
Would really appreciate any kind of support, whether it's ordering, subscribing, or just passing this along to someone you think might like it. This is how I make a living, and how we as independent publishers fight the good fight. 

Thanks in advance friends.

I shot some behind-the-scenes vignettes from Chapter One of our @lonestarbeer x @modernhuntsman film series amidst the Laguna Madre on the coast of South Texas.

We shadowed protagonist @benpaschalflyfishing to learn more about what it takes to make a living on the water and the challenges that come with it — including a delicate tension between pursuing success and protecting the resource.

I expanded this story in Volume 11 of @modernhuntsman, but for now, you can watch the film at the link in my bio. I'd love to know what you think of Ben's story.

Another volume of the @modernhuntsman publication is in the rearview mirror, and it's always a rewarding experience to see them start to show up in people's mailboxes and social feeds.⁠
⁠
Each of the eleven books we've done has had unique challenges, but like any art, we keep improving with practice. I'm unsure if we're close to the 10,000-hour mastery mark with publishing, but it definitely feels like we’ve put in the time.⁠
⁠
There is some great work in this volume, so if you're not already subscribed or ordered a single issue, you can do so at the link in my bio. We have limited extra copies, and your support helps keep independent publishing alive. ⁠
⁠
Cheers folks!

If you're in Dallas this weekend, I'd like to invite you to visit our @modernhuntsman booth at the @shopaf.com Holiday Market in Bishop Arts. When I say booth, I mean we'll have my truck there with a camp set up, some coolers, a bunch of our new magazines, and one singing shaggy dog.⁠
⁠
There are a lot of other great brands there, food, beer and liquor sponsors, and we'd love to say hello. It goes from 11-5 on both Saturday and Sunday. Tickets are free but you need to register to get in. The link is in my bio to save time or you can sort it at the entrance.⁠
⁠
Come hang out; the weather is gonna be nice!

Happy birthday to my incredible fiancé @carisfawcett. I didn’t know that a perfect match could exist until I met her, and now life just seems to make more sense.

I have never met a more dynamic, talented, enthusiastic and hilarious woman in my life, and she inspires me everyday. From the wilds of Tanzania to the hills of Scotland, the beach to the ballroom, Caris is always up for the adventure, lights up any room she is in, and will damn sure have one hell of an ensemble prepared for the occasion.

Here is to many more laughter-filled years ahead, cheers my dear!

Made it to 40.

Lots of miles and adventures packed into this wild ride to reflect on. For better or worse, I’ve managed to keep it interesting. Maybe I’ll write a book about it someday.

It’s been a really tough year, but some amazing milestones and good things have made all the tribulations worth it. Looking forward to putting 2023 in the ashtray and lighting up a fresh year soon.

A sincere thank you to everybody for the celebratory kind words the past few days to Caris and me. We love you all.
